The <b>Cinnamon-tailed Sparrow</b> (<i>Peucaea sumichrasti</i>) is a species of <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Bird" title="Bird">bird</a> in the <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Emberizidae" title="Emberizidae">Emberizidae</a> family that is endemic to <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Mexico" title="Mexico">Mexico</a>.
Its natural <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Habitat" title="Habitat">habitats</a> are subtropical or tropical dry <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Forest" title="Forest">forests</a> and subtropical or tropical dry <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Shrubland" title="Shrubland">shrubland</a>. It is threatened by <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Habitat_destruction" title="Habitat destruction">habitat loss</a>.
